body:
### Describe the bug

I can't install h5py because of some cython compile errors 

### Code to reproduce the behaviour:

To reproduce the error type this 
pip install h5py --no-build-isolation

### Expected behaviour

H5py successfully installed

### OS

Linux on termux on android

### Python version

 Python 3

### Cython version

3.0.5

### Additional context

Just ask me and i provide you the error but plz respond me as soon as possible

comment_data.body:
I believe H5py only supports Cython 0.29.x right now. They're working to fix this, but you have to use an older version of Cython currently.

In future please ask support questions on the [cython-users mailing list](https://groups.google.com/g/cython-users) instead

Also

> Just ask me and i provide you the error but plz respond me as soon as possible

Things like the error message should be *a basic part* of a bug report, not something that you provide later if asked.
